commit.message: Bumpversion 1.3.1 --> 1.3.2
Added no coverage statements for rare hard to check condiditions #45

Moved models from test_multi.py to test_models.py #45

* Previous commit did not trigger CI build since I omitted the PR reference this commit should do the trick

Added fixed random_seed and better checks to test_is_invertible_module, also added more tests

* Added better tests for is_invertible_module
* Moved most of the test models to test_models.py
* Removed TODO for injecting gradients, since this should become a new issue

WIP Refactored some variable names in the InvertibleCheckpointFunction, added gradient setting, updated is_invertible_module check #45

* Added grad injection to InvertibleCheckpointFunction to mimic backward behavior
* Added TODO for potential fixing grad injection

* Updated is_invertible_module to deal with multi input/output invertible modules
  * Added better tests for test_input_shape types
  * Allow shared tensors, but added checks which throws warnings
  * Added some TODOs

* Added is_invertible_module checks to test_multi.py

* Allow identity invertible modules that share tensors in test_revop.py
Updated docstrings for multi-input/multi-output
Added test for multi-input and multi-output invertible modules
Added support for multi-input and multi-output layers.
